{"parse":{"title":"The Smartest Guys in the Room (book)","pageid":27385227,"revid":834192141,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">The Smartest Guys in the Room <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Smartest+Guys+in+the+Room&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BBethany+McLean%5D%5D%2C+%5B%5BPeter+Elkind%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=October+13%2C+2003&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BPortfolio+Trade%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=464\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;display:none\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Bethany_McLean\" title=\"Bethany McLean\">Bethany McLean</a>, <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Peter_Elkind&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Peter Elkind (page does not exist)\">Peter Elkind</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original&#160;title</th><td>\n<i>The Smartest Guys in the Room: The Amazing Rise and Scandalous Fall of Enron</i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUnited States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subject</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Corporate_Law\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Corporate Law\">Corporate Law</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Ethics\" title=\"Ethics\">Ethics</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Fall_of_Enron\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fall of Enron\">fall of Enron</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\nNon-Fiction</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Portfolio_Trade&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Portfolio Trade (page does not exist)\">Portfolio Trade</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\nOctober 13, 2003</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nHardcover</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n464</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-59184-053-4\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-59184-053-4\">978-1-59184-053-4</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Smartest Guys in the Room: The Amazing Rise and Scandalous Fall of Enron</b></i> is a book by <a href=\"/wiki/Bethany_McLean\" title=\"Bethany McLean\">Bethany McLean</a> and Peter Elkind, first published in 2003 by <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Portfolio_Trade&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Portfolio Trade (page does not exist)\">Portfolio Trade</a>. In 2005, it was adapted into a <a href=\"/wiki/Documentary_film\" title=\"Documentary film\">documentary film</a>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Smartest Guys in the Room\">Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room</a></i>.\n</p><p>McLean and Elkind worked on the book when they both were <i>Fortune</i> senior writers. McLean had written a March 5, 2001 article for <i>Fortune</i> called, \"Is Enron overpriced?\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  \n</p><p>The book is based on hundreds of interviews and details from personal calendars, performance reviews, e-mails, and other documents. It was called \u201cThe best book about the Enron debacle to date\u201d by BusinessWeek.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It hit the New York Times bestseller list<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and was named one of <i>strategy+business</i> magazine's best business books of 2003.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>  \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room_(book)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://money.cnn.com/2006/01/13/news/companies/enronoriginal_fortune/\">\"FORTUNE archive: Is Enron Overpriced? - Jan. 19, 2006\"</a>. <i>money.cnn.com</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 December</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=money.cnn.com&amp;rft.atitle=FORTUNE+archive%3A+Is+Enron+Overpriced%3F+-+Jan.+19%2C+2006&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmoney.cnn.com%2F2006%2F01%2F13%2Fnews%2Fcompanies%2Fenronoriginal_fortune%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Smartest+Guys+in+the+Room+%28book%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2003-10-26/enron-under-two-microscopes\">\"Enron Under Two Microscopes\"</a>. 27 October 2003<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 December</span> 2017</span>  &#8211; via www.bloomberg.com.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Enron+Under+Two+Microscop